Additional Disclaimer (Privacy & Anonymity Software)

Delta-Time is provided for lawful, privacy-preserving communication purposes only.
The author(s) make no guarantees regarding the absolute anonymity, security,
or availability of this software, the Tor network, or any hidden services
created through it. Software of this kind can never guarantee perfect
anonymity or security; the user is solely responsible for evaluating whether
Delta-Time is fit for their specific threat model before relying on it.

0. ALPHA SOFTWARE — READ BEFORE USE

   Delta-Time is currently in an ALPHA stage of development. This means:

   a) The software has NOT undergone a professional, independent security
      audit. Cryptographic implementations, key handling, and network
      routing may contain undiscovered vulnerabilities.
   b) Features, protocols, storage formats, and cryptographic schemes are
      subject to change without notice and without backward compatibility
      between versions.
   c) Data loss, message loss, key loss, or temporary/permanent loss of
      connectivity or anonymity guarantees may occur without warning.
   d) Delta-Time is NOT recommended for use in situations where a failure of
      security or anonymity could result in physical harm, legal jeopardy,
      or other serious consequences to the user or any third party. Users
      operating under a high-risk threat model should not rely on this
      software at its current stage of development.
   e) "Alpha" status will be removed from this notice only upon a
      version explicitly tagged as "beta" or later by the author(s).

